<TITLE> Rain disrupts power supply in city </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 25 (bdnews24.com)  Rain disrupted power supply in the city Friday, a DESA official said. Executive engineer Mostak Ali at the control room of Dhaka Electric Supply Authority said many transformers went out of order because of the rain. It happens if there is sudden rain after a long time; sometimes local systems go out of order due to rain in the early rainy season, he added. He said demand for electricity was 3750 megawatts in the country and production was 3360 megawatts Friday. Projected load-shedding was 338 megawatts. Ali said power supply was disrupted in Lalbagh, Azimpur, Shyamoli, Paribagh, Jhigatala, Khilkhet and many other areas in the city Friday because of various reasons. bdnews
